<plot>This short subject shows 'Lissa Bengston' (qv) teaching a group of three- and four-year-olds how to swim in a pool. Miss Bengston, a member of the Royal Academy of Physical Education, Stockholm, Sweden, believes that at this age, children have no fear of the water and, therefore, can be taught to use their natural abilities to swim.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?044126</url></doc>
